"   <div id=\"basicsTopicLeft\">",
"    <div id=\"topicTitle\">",
"     Patient information: Mono, the &ldquo;kissing disease&rdquo; (The Basics)",
"    </div>",
"    <span class=\"view\">",
"     View in",
"     <a class=\"lang\" href=\"./es-419/mono-the-kissing-disease-the-basics?source=topic_page\">",
"      Spanish",
"     </a>",
"    </span>",
"    <a class=\"contributor contributor_credentials\" href=\"./authors-and-editors/patient-information\">",
"     Written by the doctors and editors at UpToDate",
"    </a>",
"    <div id=\"topicText\">",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H475485619\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What is mono?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Mono is a viral infection that causes fever, sore throat, tiredness, and swelling of the neck glands. Some people call mono \"the kissing disease.\" That&rsquo;s because kissing is one of the ways you can catch mono. It usually affects children, teenagers and young adults. &ldquo;Mono&rdquo; is short for mononucleosis.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H475485626\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       How did I get mono?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;The virus that causes mono lives in saliva. You can catch it from someone who has mono if you:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bulletCompact-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Kiss",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Share a fork, spoon, or knife",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Drink from the same glass",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H475485633\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Is there a test for mono?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Yes. Your doctor or nurse can give you a blood test to check for mono. But even if you do have mono, the test may not show the infection during the first 2 weeks of symptoms.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H475485640\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       How is mono treated?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;There is no treatment that cures mono. But medicines like",
"      <a class=\"drug drug_patient\" href=\"mobipreview.htm?19/35/20021?source=see_link\">",
"       acetaminophen",
"      </a>",
"      (sample brand name: Tylenol&reg;) or",
"      <a class=\"drug drug_patient\" href=\"mobipreview.htm?14/17/14614?source=see_link\">",
"       ibuprofen",
"      </a>",
"      (sample brand names: Advil&reg; and Motrin&reg;) can relieve the pain and fever mono causes. If you take these medicines, be sure to follow the directions on the label.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Antibiotics do not work on mono.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H475485647\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What can I do to feel better?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Get plenty of rest. And drink enough fluids so that your urine",
"      <strong>",
"      </strong>",
"      is pale yellow instead of dark yellow. Drinking fluids is really important if you are taking",
"      <a class=\"drug drug_patient\" href=\"mobipreview.htm?14/17/14614?source=see_link\">",
"       ibuprofen",
"      </a>",
"      . That&rsquo;s because ibuprofen can cause problems with your kidneys.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H475485654\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       When can I go back to work or school?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;You can go back to school or work when you feel better. But you may need to avoid sports or other physical activities for at least a month. That's because mono can cause one of the organs in your body to become bigger than it should be. This organ is called the spleen (",
"      <a class=\"graphic graphic_figure graphicRef61816 \" href=\"mobipreview.htm?36/5/36948\">",
"       figure 1",
"      </a>",
"      ). When it is too big, it can get damaged during physical activity.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      If your spleen gets big when you have mono, you will have to avoid physical activity until your doctor or nurse says you can go back to it.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H475485661\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       When will I feel better?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;You will probably start to feel better in 1 to 2 weeks. But it can be a month or more before you get back to normal. Most people get over mono with no lasting problems.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H475485668\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       More on this topic",
"      </span>",
"     </p>",
